    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nYes.\n\n### Feature description\n\nThe `vim.fn.screencol` and `vim.fn.screenrow` is useful to manage multiple floating window positions.\n\nI'm happy if it is provided as neovim API like `vim.api.nvim_screen_get_cursor`.\n\nTest case / repro:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37761",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The `vim.fn.screencol` and `vim.fn.screenrow` is useful to manage multiple floating window positions.\n\nTypically we don't want to have one-to-one API functions that are just redundant with Vimscript functions. So `nvim_ui_get_cursor({grid}, ...)` is better than `nvim_ui_get_row({grid}, ...)` + `nvim_ui_get_col({grid}, ...)`.\n\nThis would imply some way of getting the `grid` id of a tabpage, I think.\n\n\nMeanwhile, I tested screenrow() / screencol() and they always return 1 (probably because my cursor is at 1x1 after I run a `:echo screencol()` command).",
