            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Yes. Somtimes, `vim.fn.screenrow` returns invalid value.\r\nI don't know the reason but it will appear when printing some debug info by `print(...)`.\r\n\r\nIf we remove the `print('CursorMoved')`, the `screenrow` will return correct row.\r\n```\r\n_G.onCursorMoved = function()\r\n  -- print('CursorMoved')\r\n  local row = vim.fn.screenrow()\r\n  local col = vim.fn.screencol()\r\n  print(vim.inspect({\r\n    row = row,\r\n    col = col,\r\n  }))\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.cmd [[autocmd CursorMoved * call v:lua.onCursorMoved()]]\r\n```",
